Text: Thank you for calling the adverse event call center. My name is Mike, and
I'm here to help. Could you tell me your name and what you're experiencing? Hi.
My name is Lisa. I've been on that metformin for about two months now, and my stomach has
been acting weird lately. I'm sorry to hear that, Lisa. Could you
describe the symptoms you're experiencing? Sure. I've
been having some stomach discomfort. It's kind of hard to explain. It's
like b and maybe some cramp. It's been happening on and off, but
it feels unusual for me. Thank you for sharing that. Have you noticed
that these symptoms occur at a specific time? Like after taking
your medication or eating? Well, I usually take Metformin with breakfast.
I thought it might help, but I'm not sure if that's making it worse. I also started a
new probiotic around the same time. So I'm not sure if it's that or the metformin
causing this. Plus, I've always had a sensitive stomach. That's helpful
to know. Have you tried anything to ease the symptoms like changing
when or how you take your medication? I've been trying to stick to taking it with breakfast. But
someone suggested I tried taking it in the middle of the meal instead of at the start. I haven't done that
yet though. I see. It might be worth discussing this with your doctor or pharmacist
